    },
    "2p4t": {
      "id": "2p4t",
      "title": "abc",
      "body": "\n## Implementation Notes\n\nImplemented unique prefix highlighting for change IDs in the 'pebbles show' command.\n\n### Changes Made:\n1. Added 'unique_prefix_len()' function in src/commands/mod.rs:74 to calculate the minimum prefix length needed to uniquely identify a change ID among all others\n2. Added 'format_id_with_unique_prefix()' function in src/commands/mod.rs:96 to format the ID with the unique prefix in bold cyan and the rest dimmed\n3. Updated 'show' command in src/commands/show.rs:20-26 to use the new formatting\n\n### Technical Details:\n- The unique prefix is calculated by comparing the target ID against all other change IDs\n- The shortest prefix that makes the ID unique is highlighted\n- Format: unique prefix in bold cyan, remaining characters dimmed\n- Example: If change '2p4t' is the only one starting with '2', it will display as **2**p4t (with '2' bold and 'p4t' dimmed)\n\n## Log\n- 2026-02-18: Implemented unique prefix highlighting for change IDs\n",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T21:06:10.592887Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-18T21:14:31.428830Z"
    },
    "hoy9": {
      "id": "hoy9",
      "title": "Add support for issues with dependencies",
      "body": "Docket would call these epics, not the world's biggest fan of epic, but we want to track the idea of dependencies between issues and also show that in the list view. This means the list view is going to need a tree mode. so the \"list\" view should probably not draw boxes around everything - the table code should not have borders but still help us control the output (i.e. the width.)",
      "status": "draft",
      "priority": "medium",
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T22:37:31.482437Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-18T22:37:31.482437Z"
    },
    "0zu0": {
      "id": "0zu0",
      "title": "add plan command",
      "body": "The idea of the plan command is we go ahead and review the contents of the issue and then invoke open code with our custom plan command, which allows us to further refine the issues before we approve them.",
      "status": "draft",
      "priority": "medium",
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T22:40:38.651291Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-18T22:40:38.651291Z"
    },
    "oija": {
      "id": "oija",
      "title": "Add output feedback to opencode run command",
      "body": "\n## Goal\nAdd output feedback to the 'pebbles start' command so users know when opencode is working.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [x] Add --print-logs flag to pebbles start command\n- [x] --print-logs flag passes through to opencode run command\n- [x] On non-Unix systems, stdout/stderr is inherited when --print-logs is set\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nAdded a new --print-logs flag to the 'pebbles start' command:\n\n### Changes Made:\n1. **src/cli.rs:52-54** - Added --print-logs flag to Start command with help text\n2. **src/main.rs:27,34** - Updated Start command handler to pass print_logs parameter\n3. **src/commands/start.rs:13,78-80,84,89-101** - \n   - Updated function signature to accept print_logs parameter\n   - Pass --print-logs to opencode when flag is set\n   - On non-Unix systems, inherit stdout/stderr when flag is set\n\n### Usage:\n```\npebbles start <id> --print-logs\n```\n\nThis will show opencode's output/logs to the console instead of running silently.\n\n## Log\n- 2026-02-19: Added --print-logs flag to pebbles start command\n",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "high",
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T22:49:43.672257Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-19T13:35:13.125266Z"
    }
  },
